Glazed Diced Citron





Glazed Diced Citron











Pin It5




Share10




Tweet




+12






Kosher






This will be used for multiple batches of "Grandma Sommerman's citron-almond bread."  She used to make it at Christmas but we make it 3-4 times a year (in 5 loaf batches) freeze the extra and have it toasted for breakfast.  If you have anyone compiling recipes, I'd be glad to share it if you send me an email address.  I am so happy to have found you, because other than November-December, citron is almost impossible to find and I never  manage to buy enough.  Thank you!
Gloria Puester
Gloria, Aurora, CO
May 2, 2017





4.9 out of 5 stars
              

174 customer reviews »







Our glazed diced citron is a must-have for fruitcakes. It also lends a sweet flavor and elegant look to cookies and other desserts. Glazed citron has an exceptional citrus flavor with a delectable sweetness. Make it a staple in your kitchen around the holidays or anytime of year.
















